com.twofortyfouram.test.provider

Class MockableContentProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.content.ContentProvider
      • com.twofortyfouram.test.provider.MockableContentProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentCallbacks, ComponentCallbacks2

    @NotThreadSafe
public final class MockableContentProvider
extends ContentProvider
    A content provider whose basic methods of query, insert, update, delete, and call are easily mockable. Note that after instantiation, attachInfo(Context, ProviderInfo) must be called manually. To bypass this limitation, consider using the helper method newMockProvider(Context, String).

      • newMockProvider

        @NonNull
public static MockableContentProvider newMockProvider(@NonNull
                                                               Context baseContext,
                                                               @NonNull
                                                               String authority)
        Helper method to make using the MockableContentProvider less verbose in some standard use cases.
        Parameters:
        baseContext - Base context.
        authority - Content authority.
        Returns:
        A provider with a context whose content resolver will resolve authority to the returned ContentProvider. Note: Be sure to use ContentProvider.getContext() to retrieve the appropriate context for querying the ContentResolver.
